Durban - Grandmother Devikiamma Devi Pillay is still missing in India. The retired 76-year-old dressmaker, formerly of Isipingo, was last seen on February 24 boarding a train from Mumbai to Bhubaneswari (Orissa). Her son Kenny left for India last week to head a search party. The grandmother of four, of Gauteng, who has been travelling since November, was supposed to visit friends in India but when she failed to arrive, they notified her family in South Africa. Nelson Kgwete, the directorate for media liaison at the Department of International Relations and Cooperation, said: “The matter is being taken up with the Indian police by the SA Consulate-General in Mumbai.” POST